        "heading": "Sulfur gas is the real cause of bad breath.",
        "subheading": "<p>Most mouthwashes mask the symptom. SmartMouth™ eliminates the cause — then prevents it from coming back for 24 hours.</p>",
        "detail_heading": "Why sulfur gas smells so bad",
        "detail_body": "<p>The compounds bacteria produce — specifically hydrogen sulfide and methyl mercaptan — are among the most odorous substances known. Even at concentrations of just a few parts per billion, they’re immediately detectable by the human nose. That’s why bad breath can feel so persistent: the source is microscopic, but the smell is instant.</p>",
        "virus_image": "shopify://shop_images/sulfur-gas0virus.webp",
